# Ad Event Stream - Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
Apache Flink 1.18 + Kotlin event stream processing for Facebook ads.
Multi-module Gradle project with SSP and DSP pipelines.

## Modules
- `stream-common/` - Shared models, serialization, utilities
- `ssp-stream/` - SSP event aggregation + S3 storage jobs
- `dsp-stream/` - DSP event aggregation + S3 storage jobs

## Tech Stack
- Kotlin 1.9.22, Java 11 target
- Apache Flink 1.18.1 (DataStream API)
- Kafka connector for Flink
- Parquet + S3 for data storage
- Helm charts for K8s deployment

## Commands
- Build: `./gradlew build`
- Test: `./gradlew test`
- Lint: `./gradlew detekt`
- Build fat JAR: `./gradlew shadowJar`
- Deploy: `helm upgrade -f helm/ad-event-stream/values.yaml`

## Coding Patterns
- Use Kotlin data classes for models
- Use sealed classes for event type hierarchy
- Flink jobs in `job/` packages, functions in `function/` packages
- ProcessFunction for filtering with side output (dead letter)
- AggregateFunction + WindowFunction for windowed aggregation
- All Flink operators must have uid() set for savepoint compatibility

## Do NOT
- Do not change serialization schema without coordinating with ad-event-receiver
- Do not modify Helm values.yaml without ops review
- Do not remove Flink operator uid() values (breaks savepoint restore)
- Do not use Flink's Table API (we use DataStream API only)

## Kafka Topics (Input)
- `ad.events.ssp` - SSP raw events
- `ad.events.dsp` - DSP raw events

## Kafka Topics (Output)
- `ad.metrics.ssp.aggregated` - SSP aggregated metrics
- `ad.metrics.dsp.aggregated` - DSP aggregated metrics
